display="inline"><![CDATA[TA]]></fr:tex> by its sub-objects <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[TF^p(A)]]></fr:tex> (these are sub-objects since <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[T]]></fr:tex> is left exact).
    If <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[\operatorname {Gr}_F(A)]]></fr:tex> is <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[T]]></fr:tex>-acyclic, then the <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[F^p(A)]]></fr:tex> are <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[T]]></fr:tex>-acyclic as successive extensions of <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[T]]></fr:tex>-acyclic objects.
    The image under <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[T]]></fr:tex> of the sequence
    <fr:tex
display="block"><![CDATA[       0       \to  F^{p+1}(A)       \to  F^p(A)       \to  \operatorname {Gr}^p(A)       \to  0     ]]></fr:tex>
    
    is thus exact, and

