display="inline"><![CDATA[A]]></fr:tex> be an object endowed with finite filtrations <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[F]]></fr:tex> and <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[W]]></fr:tex> such that <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[\operatorname {Gr}_F\operatorname {Gr}_W A]]></fr:tex> are <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[T]]></fr:tex>-acyclic.
    The objects <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[\operatorname {Gr}_FA]]></fr:tex> and <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[\operatorname {Gr}_WA]]></fr:tex> are then <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[T]]></fr:tex>-acyclic, as well as the <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[F^q(A)\cap  W^p(A)]]></fr:tex>.
    The sequences
    <fr:tex
display="block"><![CDATA[       0       \to  T(F^q\cap  W^{p+1})       \to  T(F^q\cap  W^p)       \to  T((F^q\cap  W^p)/(F^q\cap  W^{p+1}))       \to  0     ]]></fr:tex>
    are thus exact, and <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[T(F^q(\operatorname {Gr}_W^p(A)))]]></fr:tex> is the image in <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[T(\operatorname {Gr}_W^p(A))]]></fr:tex> of <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[T(F^p\cap  W^q)]]></fr:tex>.
    The diagram
    <fr:tex
display="block"><![CDATA[       \begin {CD}         T(F^q\cap  W^p) @>>> T(F^q\operatorname {Gr}_W^pA) @>>> T\operatorname {Gr}_W^pA       \\@V{\cong }VV @. @VV{\cong }V       \\TF^q\cap  TW^p @= TF^q\cap  TW^p @>>> \operatorname {Gr}_{TW}^pTA       \end {CD}     ]]></fr:tex>
    then shows that the isomorphism in <fr:ref
addr="hodge-theory-ii-1.4.2.1"
href="hodge-theory-ii-1.4.2.1.xml"
taxon="Equation"
number="1.4.2.1" /> relative to <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[W]]></fr:tex> sends the filtration <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[\operatorname {Gr}_{TW}(TF)]]></fr:tex> to the filtration <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[T(\operatorname {Gr}_W(F))]]></fr:tex>.</fr:p></fr:mainmatter><fr:backmatter /></fr:tree></fr:mainmatter><fr:backmatter /></fr:tree></fr:backmatter></fr:tree>